article.headline: DePaul 64, Liberty 63
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. -- Dar Tucker scored 16, including a pair of free throws with 1.1 seconds left, as DePaul snapped a four-game losing steak with a 64-63 win over Liberty on Wednesday night. Mac Koshwal scored 14 and Devin Hill had 13 rebounds for the Blue Demons (5-4), which squandered an 18-point lead in the second half. Seth Curry, who came in averaging 21.4 points per game to lead all true freshman, scored 16 for Liberty (7-3). Anthony Smith scored 15, and Brolin Floyd and Kyle Ohman each added 10 for the Flames. Ohman's 3-pointer with 2:13 remaining capped a 8-0 run that gave Liberty its first lead of the second half, 61-60. Liberty made 9-of-17 3-pointers after halftime and cut DePaul's lead to 55-53 with 7:03 remaining. The Blue Demons led 39-23 at the half.
